  "header": "Voice, agents, robotics, and open AI infrastructure move closer to daily work",
  "friendlyHeader": "AI tools are getting more useful for real everyday tasks",
  "summary": "Today’s issue follows AI systems becoming more useful in the places people actually work: live voice, managed agents, robotics, classroom planning, consumer media tools, enterprise-owned agent stacks, and the data pipelines behind them. The practical theme is control — better interfaces, more inspectable data, cheaper adaptation, and tools that keep humans in the loop.",
  "friendlySummary": "Today’s stories show AI becoming easier to talk to, easier to build into work, and more useful in robots, schools, photos, and business systems. The big idea: AI helps most when people can understand it, guide it, and use it safely.",
